        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 1:44PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Crater Lake Campground, or 20 miles north of Chester,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aspen Grove Campground, Crater Lake Campground, Ca 44 At
Shasta-Lassen Co Line, Christie Campground, Merrill Campground, and
Eagle Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
